               <msContents>
                  <summary>F. i v(erso): record of an event on Nahase 3. F. iir: Asmat prayer against hail and lightning, ጸሎተ፡ በረድ፡ ወመብረቅ።  F. ii v: Asmat prayer for protection. F. iii r-iv r: Prayer to God, “For the Sake of the Honor and Covenant of Our Lady, Virgin Mary,” በእንተ፡ ዕበያ፡ ወክብራ፡ ወኪዳና፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ ድንግል፡ ; Ff. iv r-v: Hymn to Mary, “I Prostrate Before You,” እሰግድ፡ ለኪ፡. Répertoire 336/338. F. v r: record of an event on Nahase 3, 1916, referring to Grazmač and Qängazmač. F<locus target="#1r"/>-125v: Harp of Praise, Arganonä Wǝddase, አርጋኖነ፡ ውዳሴ፡, arranged for the days of the week. Pontus Leander, `Arganona Ueddase nach Handschriften in Uppsala, Berlin, Tübingen und Frankfurt a. M. Göteborgs Högskolas Årsskrift 28.3 (Leipzig 1922). Monday (<locus target="#1r"/>), Tuesday (<locus target="#22r"/>), Wednesday (<locus target="#42v"/>), F<locus target="#64r"/>-v: One Miracle of Mary.How the Virgin delivered from devils the soul of a scribe who was engaged in writing a copy of the Book of her Miracles. This scribe had a brother who had sinned, but not knowing him they seized the innocent man and tried to carry him off to hell (Budge, XVIII; Princeton Ethiopic MS 41, f<locus target="#66v"/>–67v; EMDL 681, f<locus target="#83rv"/>) Thursday (<locus target="#65r"/>), Friday (<locus target="#85v"/>), Saturday (106r), Sunday (<locus target="#116r"/>). A Miracle of Mary, incomplete at the end. <locus target="#127r"/>. Record in a later hand, complete with fingerprint.</summary>
